<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-22T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3281: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-22T09:00:00-05:00">June 22,
                                    1932—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>78. Congress yesterday passed administration measure suspending
                            constitutional guarantees for 1 year and authorizing the Executive to
                            extend suspension for additional 2 years if necessary. The apparent
                            purpose of the measure is to serve notice on the opposition that the
                                <persName corresp="#p_MMGG1">Machado</persName> Government intends
                            to continue to proceed with a strong hand.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>